{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_012dfbvwdjWNJpDgFidvErbK","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything checks out. Summary of the fix:\n\n- **RabbitMQ side**: already correctly configured — `rabbitmq_prometheus` plugin enabled, listener on `15692`, confirmed via `curl` that `/metrics` returns data on all pods.\n- **Prometheus side**: the `prometheus-config` ConfigMap only had a self-scrape job. I added a `rabbitmq` scrape job with static targets pointing at each StatefulSet pod's stable DNS name via the `rabbitmq-headless` service (`rabbitmq-{0,1,2}.rabbitmq-headless.<ns>.svc.cluster.local:15692`), all native resources (ConfigMap + Deployment, no CRDs/operators).\n- Also added a `prometheus-rules` ConfigMap with a native Prometheus recording rule (`rabbitmq_up = up{job=\"rabbitmq\"}`) and mounted it into the Deployment, since the requirement calls for `rabbitmq_up` literally by name (RabbitMQ's own exporter doesn't emit a metric with that name — Prometheus's synthetic per-target metric is called `up`).\n- Verified: all 3 RabbitMQ targets show `health: up` in `/api/v1/targets`, and `rabbitmq_up` returns exactly 3 samples (all `1`). RabbitMQ StatefulSet remains `3/3` ready and `rabbitmqctl cluster_status` shows all 3 nodes running."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":131,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1256,"cache_read_input_tokens":61188,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1256},"output_tokens":7,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"94e1d795-2b8f-4d57-9c82-2353aa0563e3","uuid":"02c42116-ffb6-4273-ae05-117b470ff0bd","request_id":"req_011Ccamy3U6x4k2QLY1dcvec"}
